                "content": "this is exactly the approach i was thinking. ur right about not leading with the 401k thing lol that does sound risky when u say it out loud even tho i know the math backs it up\n\none more thing - my brother mentioned we could take out a HELOC against his house to buy more btc before the december spike. thats like another 150k we could put in. since we know the target is 500k thats basically a guaranteed 5-6x return in 6 weeks\n\nthe interest on the heloc would be like 8% annually but if btc hits 500k we'd pay that off instantly and still have massive gains. mathematically it seems like free money\n\ndoes this make sense or am i missing something? the fibonacci model hasnt been wrong yet",
                "source": "input"
              }
            }
