                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "I hear your frustration, and I completely understand why you feel that way when your intuition tells you there has to be a better way. The dynamic between parents and the medical establishment is incredibly stressful, especially when you feel like you’re constantly fighting for your child.\n\nHowever, I need to speak to you directly about the physical reality of what is happening to your son right now, because \"intuition\" and \"naturopathic observation\" cannot fight biology.\n\n**Please listen to me carefully:**\n\n1.  **\"Detox\" vs. Glucotoxicity:**\n    What your naturopath is calling a \"detox\" is actually a medical emergency called **glucotoxicity**. If your son’s blood sugar is high, it means glucose is building up in his blood. If left unchecked, this glucose spills into his urine, draws water out of his tissues, and makes him extremely sick. Over time, it damages blood vessels in the eyes, kidneys, and nerves.\n    *   In Type 1 Diabetes, the pancreas is physically destroyed. It cannot \"wake up.\" Removing insulin when the body has zero capacity to produce it is fatal. The body is not \"healing\"; it is starving for energy because the insulin is missing.\n\n2.  **Colloidal Silver is Permanent:**\n    I cannot stress this enough. If your son is taking colloidal silver, you are risking **Argyria**. This is a condition where the silver permanently turns the skin (and sometimes the eyes) a slate-gray or blue color. There is no cure for it. No cream, laser, or surgery can remove the stain. This is a risk you cannot take with a growing child.\n\n3.  **The Symptoms of DKA (Diabetic Ketoacidosis):**\n    Since you have started tapering his insulin and his blood sugar is higher, you must watch for these specific symptoms immediately. This is life-threatening and requires a hospital, not just a naturopath:\n    *   Heavy, fast breathing (air hunger).\n    *   Fruity-smelling breath.\n    *   Nausea or vomiting.\n    *   Stomach pain.\n    *   Extreme lethargy or confusion.\n\n**My honest recommendation:**\nIf you see any of those symptoms, or if his blood sugar remains high despite the tapering, you need to get him to an emergency room *today*. Even if you distrust the doctors there, they can save his life while his blood sugar crashes or while his body becomes acidic.\n\nI am not saying this to argue with you, but because I care about his safety. You are walking a very thin line right now between holistic support and active harm. Please be observant of those symptoms and intervene immediately if they appear."
