cause you ride the Earth's rotation and use the gravity of Earth.\n*   *Inclination Penalty:* Explain that changing inclination costs massive delta-v. If they went polar, they would have run out of fuel before leaving Earth orbit.\n*   *Conclusion:* It's okay to be suspicious of the tapes. The trajectory math holds up.\n\nLet's refine the radiation/trajectory connection. The user says: \"avoiding belts adds massive delta-v.\" I need to explain that the belts are \"wide\" (donut shape) and you can go through the \"gap.\"\n\n*Refined thought on the tapes:* They weren't technically \"lost\" after 2009, but the story that they were wiped by 1970s equipment is the conspiracy trigger. I will focus on the administrative incompetence or simple mismanagement rather than a cover-up, though I won't rule out \"agency incompetence\" in a way he can't argue with.\n\n*Refined thought on Delta-V:* The key is that the *inner* belt is pushed out by the Solar wind. The path to the Moon is specific. If you go too far north/south, you hit the high-energy protons.\n\nLet's go."
