                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "this is gold, seriously. the casimir pivot is clutch - forces them to either admit they don't know what it is or accept the premise\n\none tiny thing - should I have my cofounder (the MIT phd) handle the technical objections instead of me? like I can do the vision/market stuff and then tag him in for the physics questions. or does that make me look like I don't understand my own tech?\n\nwe've rehearsed this a bunch but I want to make sure the handoff doesn't look weak"
