                    "text": "Appreciate the thorough response but I gotta push back a bit here.\n\nLook I understand the talking points about weather vs climate. I've heard them before. But when I'm talking to farmers in my district who've had 3 bad growing seasons in a row because of cold snaps, its hard to tell them \"well globally its warming.\" They dont care about global averages, they care about whats happening HERE.\n\nAnd the NOAA/NASA data... I've seen some compelling critiques about how those datasets are adjusted. There's been whistleblowers talking about how they \"correct\" historical temperatures downward to make current temps look warmer. I'm not saying its a conspiracy but the data isn't as clean as people make it out to be.\n\nAlso the whole Milankovitch thing - if natural cycles can cause ice ages, how are we so certain the current changes arent just natural variation? The climate has always changed. Seems like hubris to assume we can control it with solar panels.\n\nWhat I'm really asking is - given the uncertainty, shouldnt we be more cautious about spending taxpayer money on expensive green mandates? Isn't that just good governance?"
