site is often argued: some critics claim adjustments are *upward* to create the warming trend. I need to clarify that adjustments smooth out noise, not fabricate heat. Urban stations (cities) are adjusted down because cities get hotter over time (UHI), which would make the past look colder by comparison. If they weren't adjusted, the warming would actually look *stronger*. I need to explain this clearly so the user understands why critics might see \"corrections.\"\n\nLet's write it."
